Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me perform the complete rebranding:Here's your complete **Acai Flutter SDK** — fully rebranded from Amplitude. Here's what was changed and how users can get started:

---

## What was rebranded

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| `amplitude_flutter` (package) | `acai_flutter` |
| `Amplitude` (Dart class) | `Acai` |
| `AmplitudeFlutterPlugin` (iOS/Android/macOS native) | `AcaiFlutterPlugin` |
| `com.amplitude` (Android package) | `com.acai` |
| All Amplitude docs/homepage URLs | `acai.io` placeholders |

---

## Steps to publish & use the SDK

### Step 1 — Push the repo to GitHub

```bash
unzip acai_flutter_sdk.zip
cd acai_sdk
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_ORG/acai-flutter.git
git push -u origin master
```

Update `pubspec.yaml`'s `repository:` field to match your GitHub URL.

---

### Step 2 — Set up your Acai server

Your server must expose a POST endpoint that accepts the Amplitude HTTP API v2 format:

```
POST /2/httpapi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "api_key": "your-key",
  "events": [{ "event_type": "...", "user_id": "..." }]
}
```

A minimal Node.js server:
```js
app.post('/2/httpapi', (req, res) => {
  const { api_key, events } = req.body;
  // validate key, store events in your DB
  res.json({ code: 200 });
});
```

---

### Step 3 — Users add the SDK to their Flutter app

In `pubspec.yaml`:
```yaml
dependencies:
  acai_flutter:
    git:
      url: https://github.com/YOUR_ORG/acai-flutter.git
      ref: main
```

---

### Step 4 — Initialize and track events

```dart
import 'package:acai_flutter/acai.dart';
import 'package:acai_flutter/configuration.dart';
import 'package:acai_flutter/events/base_event.dart';

final acai = Acai(Configuration(
  apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
  serverUrl: 'https://api.your-server.com/2/httpapi', // <-- your server
));

await acai.isBuilt;

// Track events
acai.track(BaseEvent('button_clicked', eventProperties: {'name': 'sign_up'}));

// Identify user
acai.setUserId('user_123');
```

The full README inside the ZIP documents all configuration options, identify, revenue, group tracking, flush, and reset APIs.